5) UI Acceptance Criteria
☐ Horizontal “raised card” layout for Planner | Timer | Supplies | Progress.
☐ Selecting zones/presets creates a realistic plan (≤1s perceived).
☐ Checklist steps have tooltips (tools, safety, drill suggestions).
☐ Timers control pacing; voice + toast cues; survives route changes.
☐ Supplies panel shows delta + “Make at home” recipes; one-click Print/Apply.
☐ Calendar sync respects Hebrew feast days and Sabbath; auto-suggest reschedule.
☐ Role assignment shows fair rotation; streaks & rewards increment correctly.

6) Domain Preferences & Constraints
- Fragrance sensitivity: prefer unscented; avoid mixing bleach/ammonia; caution vinegar on stone.
- Pets & kids: floor/low-shelf toxins → swap to safer options; add doors/gates steps.
- Material care: stone, wood, stainless, glass, fabric; surface-safe cleaners only.
- Feast days/Sabbath: block cleaning sessions (or suggest “preparation day”).
- Time windows: Morning shine (windows/mirrors), Evening reset (kitchen/entry), Weekly deep clean per zone.
- HR goal: light (Zone 1–2), moderate (Zone 2–3), vigorous (Zone 3–4) — micro-drills inserted accordingly.

7) Event Contract (emit/subscribe)
Emit:
  • cleaning.session.started|paused|resumed|completed
  • cleaning.step.completed ({stepId, zoneId, ts, hrSample?})
  • supplies.delta.applied ({patchId, items})
  • cleaning.fitness.enabled ({targetZone})
  • calendar.synced ({events})
  • rewards.redeemed ({points})
Subscribe:
  • user.prefs.updated → rebuild plan/timers
  • inventory.low → suggest make-at-home or purchase
  • calendar.updated → reschedule conflicts
  • hebrewCalendar.updated → recompute safe windows

